Description: Selling arguably the most beautiful guitar from my collection, but I need to free up some funds and space, so I’m letting some of my more expensive ones go. I don’t even know where to start with this guitar. I could stare at the caramel-mocha top forever. It’s impossible to capture the full scale of the flame top in photos. It shows even more flame in certain lights and also reflects as a lighter or darker shade of brown because of how much contrasting flame there is. The single bound top and the Paua Birds inlays makes it a true work of art. Playability is insanely good. I just had it setup by Dr. Jon in Round Rock - which probably means nothing to most of you, but he is one of the most highly regarded luthiers in the Austin area and the guitar actually feels like it got plek’d. Fast and low action with perfect intonation. The pickups are a HFS Treble in the bridge and a PRS Vintage Bass in the neck. Neck carve is their “wide/thin” profile. Everything is 100% factory stock, no modifications have been made. And it’s dead mint. The only signs of wear are very light finish swirls on the back, not even enough to be considered buckle rash. It comes with the trem bar, factory hard shell case and some original docs as well. Check my feedback and buy with confidence. Free shipping to the continental 48, please message me with any questions.
Title: 2004 Paul Reed Smith Custom 24 Artist Package Birds with Case
